title: Independent candidate Usama Mela wins NA-83 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate, Usama Ahmed Mela has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-83, Sargodha-II by securing 136,566 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Pakistan Muslim League-Nawaz candidate, Mohsin Shahnawaz Ranjha, who bagged 98,700 votes.
The votersâ€™ turn-out remained 52.55%.
